# Git Workflow Rules

## Branch Structure
- `main` — production only → deploys to app.vanyshr.com
- `sandbox` — active development, push here freely
- `dev/<issue-name>` — isolated work, always branch from `sandbox`

## Critical Rules
- NEVER commit directly to `main`
- NEVER force push to `main`
- `dev/*` branches always branch from `sandbox`, never from `main`
- Merge order: `dev/*` → `sandbox` → `main`
- Only merge `sandbox` → `main` when explicitly instructed

## Before Any Commit
1. Confirm current branch (`git branch`)
2. If on `main`, switch to `sandbox` first
3. Never stage: `.env.local`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `dist/`, `.turbo/`

## Commit Message Format
```
<type>: <short description>
```
- `feat` — new feature
- `fix` — bug fix
- `chore` — deps, config, cleanup
- `refactor` — restructure, no behavior change
- `style` — UI/CSS only
- `docs` — documentation only

## Vercel Previews
Every push to `sandbox` or `dev/*` creates a Vercel preview deployment automatically.
Test on the preview URL before merging to `main`.

